                        <p>The census is how we count people and find out how they live. The information we collect helps to build a picture of our society.</p>
                        <p>The UN recommends that countries hold a census at least once every 10 years. That’s what happens here in the United Kingdom, where we have three separate censuses:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>The England and Wales census is run by the <a href="">Office for National Statistics</a></li>
                            <li>Northern Ireland’s census is run by the <a href="">Northern Ireland Statistics and Research Agency</a></li>
